{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Book",
  "title": "The Book",
  "summary": "On Bespin, the xenoarchaeologist Paul Nighman returns to the apartment of the enigmatic Ylsa to examine an ancient tome she has offered for sale. Over a lavish breakfast, Paul carefully studies the gilded, illustrated volume and concludes it is genuine and roughly 7,480 years old, far older than its previous appraisal. Ylsa abruptly tries to give him the book for free, then reveals the truth: she is bound by contract to a Hutt named Ullo, the tome is secretly her own, and she had hoped its sale would help buy her freedom. Paul, refusing to simply take it, learns of her forged-document and slicing expertise from her days in an anti-Imperial resistance. He proposes an equal partnership: she will secure permits and Imperial clearance for a covert expedition to Athaniss, splitting the proceeds four ways. Ylsa agrees to consider it, and the two part with the deal tentatively struck and mutual suspicion lingering.",
